 436:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c ****     uint8 tmpReg;
 437:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c ****     tmpReg = ADC_DelSig_1_DSM_BUF1_REG & (uint8)~ADC_DelSig_1_DSM_GAIN_MASK;
 438:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c ****     tmpReg |= (uint8)(gain << ADC_DelSig_1_DSM_GAIN_SHIFT) & ADC_DelSig_1_DSM_GAIN_MASK;
 439:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c ****     ADC_DelSig_1_DSM_BUF1_REG = tmpReg;
 440:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** }
 441:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** 
 442:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** 
 443:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** /*******************************************************************************
 444:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** * Function Name: ADC_DelSig_1_SetCoherency
 445:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** ********************************************************************************
 446:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *
 447:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** * Summary:
 448:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *  This function allows the user to change which of the ADC's 3 word
 449:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *  result will trigger a coherency unlock. The ADC's result will not be
 450:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *  updated until the set byte is read either by the ADC or DMA. 
 451:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *  By default the LSB is the coherency byte for right alignment data format. 
 452:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *  The middle or high byte is set automatically depend on left alignment 
 453:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *  configuration for DMA data transfer.
 454:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *  If DMA or if a custom API requires different byte to be read the last,
 455:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *  this API should be used to set the last byte of the ADC result that is read. 
 456:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *  If a multibyte read is performed either by DMA or the ARM processor, the
 457:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *  coherency can be set to any byte in the last word read.
 458:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *
 459:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** * Parameters:
 460:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *  coherency:  Two bit value to set the coherency bit.
 461:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *           00-Coherency checking off
 462:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *           01-low byte is key byte
 463:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *           02-middle byte is the key byte
 464:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *           03-high byte is the key byte
 465:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *
 466:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** * Return:
 467:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *  None
 468:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *
 469:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *******************************************************************************/
 470:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** void ADC_DelSig_1_SetCoherency(uint8 coherency) 
 471:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** {
 472:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c ****     uint8 tmpReg;
 473:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** 
 474:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c ****     tmpReg = ADC_DelSig_1_DEC_COHER_REG & (uint8)~ADC_DelSig_1_DEC_SAMP_KEY_MASK;
 475:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c ****     tmpReg |= coherency & ADC_DelSig_1_DEC_SAMP_KEY_MASK;
 476:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c ****     ADC_DelSig_1_DEC_COHER_REG = tmpReg;
 477:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** }
 478:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** 
 479:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** 
 480:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** /*******************************************************************************
 481:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** * Function Name: ADC_DelSig_1_SetGCOR
 482:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** ********************************************************************************
 483:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *
 484:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** * Summary:
 485:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *  Calculates a new GCOR value and writes it into the GCOR register. 
 486:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *  The GCOR value is a 16-bit value that represents a gain of 0 to 2. 
 487:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *  The ADC result is multiplied by this value before it is placed in the ADC 
ARM GAS  C:\Users\Admin\AppData\Local\Temp\ccGnFHMB.s 			page 10


 488:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *  output registers. The numerical format for the GCOR value is:
 489:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *  0x0000 -> 0.000
 490:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *  0x8000 -> 1.000
 491:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *  0xFFFF -> 1.99997
 492:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *  When executing the function, the old GCOR value is multiplied by
 493:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *  gainAdjust and reloaded into the GCOR register.
 494:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *
 495:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** * Parameters:
 496:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *  gainAdjust:  floating point value to set GCOR registers.
 497:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *
 498:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** * Return:
 499:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *  uint8: 0 - if GCOR value is within the expected range.
 500:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *         1 - the correction value is outside GCOR value range of
 501:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *             0.00 to 1.9999.
 502:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *
 503:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** * Side Effects:  The GVAL register is set to the amount of valid bits in the
 504:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *                GCOR  register minus one. If GVAL is 15 (0x0F), all 16 bits
 505:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *                of the GCOR registers will be valid. If for example GVAL is
 506:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *                11 (0x0B) only 12 bits will be valid. The least 4 bits will
 507:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *                be lost when the GCOR value is shifted 4 places to the right.
 508:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *
 509:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** ******************************************************************************/
 510:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** uint8 ADC_DelSig_1_SetGCOR(float32 gainAdjust) 
 511:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** {
 512:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c ****     uint16 tmpReg;
 513:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c ****     uint8 status;
 514:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c ****     float32 tmpValue;
 515:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** 
 516:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c ****     tmpReg = ADC_DelSig_1_gcor[ADC_DelSig_1_Config - 1u].gcor;
 517:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c ****     tmpValue = ((float32)tmpReg / (float32)ADC_DelSig_1_IDEAL_GAIN_CONST);
 518:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c ****     tmpValue = tmpValue * gainAdjust;
 519:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** 
 520:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c ****     if (tmpValue > 1.9999)
 521:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c ****     {
 522:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c ****         status = 1u;
 523:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c ****     }
 524:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c ****     else
 525:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c ****     {
 526:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c ****         tmpValue *= (float32)ADC_DelSig_1_IDEAL_GAIN_CONST;
 527:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** 		tmpReg = (uint16)tmpValue;
 528:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c ****         CY_SET_REG16(ADC_DelSig_1_DEC_GCOR_16B_PTR, tmpReg);
 529:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c ****         /* Update gain array to be used by SelectConfiguration() API */
 530:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c ****        ADC_DelSig_1_gcor[ADC_DelSig_1_Config - 1u].gcor = tmpReg;
 531:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** 
 532:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c ****         status = 0u;
 533:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** 
 534:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c ****     }
 535:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c ****     return(status);
 536:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** }
 537:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** 
 538:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** 
 539:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** /******************************************************************************
 540:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** * Function Name: ADC_DelSig_1_ReadGCOR
 541:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *******************************************************************************
 542:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *
 543:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** * Summary:
 544:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *  This API returns the current GCOR register value, normalized based on the
ARM GAS  C:\Users\Admin\AppData\Local\Temp\ccGnFHMB.s 			page 11


 545:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *  GVAL register settings.
 546:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *  For example, if the GCOR value is 0x0812 and the GVAL register is set to 
 547:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *  11 (0x0B) then the returned value will be shifted by for bits to the left.
 548:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *  (Actual GCOR value = 0x0812, returned value = 0x8120)
 549:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *
 550:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** * Parameters:
 551:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *  None
 552:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *
 553:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** * Return:
 554:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *  uint16:  Normalized GCOR value.
 555:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *
 556:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *******************************************************************************/
 557:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** uint16 ADC_DelSig_1_ReadGCOR(void) 
 558:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** {
 559:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c ****     uint8 gValue;
 560:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c ****     uint16 gcorValue;
 561:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** 
 562:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c ****     gValue = ADC_DelSig_1_DEC_GVAL_REG;
 563:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c ****     gcorValue = CY_GET_REG16(ADC_DelSig_1_DEC_GCOR_16B_PTR);
 564:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** 
 565:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c ****     if (gValue < ADC_DelSig_1_MAX_GVAL)
 566:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c ****     {
 567:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c ****         gcorValue <<= ADC_DelSig_1_MAX_GVAL - gValue;
 568:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c ****     }
 569:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** 
 570:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c ****     return gcorValue;
 571:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** }
 572:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** 
 573:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** 
 574:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** /*******************************************************************************
 575:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** * Function Name: ADC_DelSig_1_StartConvert
 576:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** ********************************************************************************
 577:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *
 578:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** * Summary:
 579:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *  Forces the ADC to initiate a conversion. If in the "Single Sample"
 580:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *  mode, one conversion will be performed then the ADC will halt. If in
 581:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *  one of the other three conversion modes, the ADC will run
 582:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *  continuously until the ADC_Stop() or ADC_StopConvert() is called.
 583:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *
 584:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** * Parameters:
 585:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *  None
 586:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *
 587:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** * Return:
 588:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *  None
 589:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *
 590:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *******************************************************************************/
 591:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** void ADC_DelSig_1_StartConvert(void) 
 592:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** {
 593:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c ****     /* Start the conversion */
 594:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c ****     ADC_DelSig_1_DEC_CR_REG |= ADC_DelSig_1_DEC_START_CONV;
 595:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** }
 596:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** 
 597:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** 
 598:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** /*******************************************************************************
 599:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** * Function Name: ADC_DelSig_1_StopConvert
 600:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** ********************************************************************************
 601:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *
ARM GAS  C:\Users\Admin\AppData\Local\Temp\ccGnFHMB.s 			page 12


 602:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** * Summary:
 603:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *  Forces the ADC to stop all conversions. If the ADC is in the middle of a
 604:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *  conversion, the ADC will be reset and not provide a result for that partial
 605:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *  conversion.
 606:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *
 607:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** * Parameters:
 608:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *  None
 609:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *
 610:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** * Return:
 611:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *  None
 612:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *
 613:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *******************************************************************************/
 614:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** void ADC_DelSig_1_StopConvert(void) 
 615:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** {
 616:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c ****     /* Stop all conversions */
 617:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c ****     ADC_DelSig_1_DEC_CR_REG &= (uint8)~ADC_DelSig_1_DEC_START_CONV;
 618:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** }
 619:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** 
 620:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** 
 621:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** /*******************************************************************************
 622:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** * Function Name: ADC_DelSig_1_IsEndConversion
 623:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** ********************************************************************************
 624:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *
 625:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** * Summary:
 626:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *  Checks the status that the most recently started conversion has completed.
 627:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *  The status is cleared by any of ADC_GetResult8(), ADC_GetResult16() or 
 628:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *  ADC_GetResult32() API.
 629:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *  This function provides the programmer with two options. In one mode this 
 630:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *  function immediately returns with the conversion status. In the other mode,
 631:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *  the function does not return (blocking) until the conversion has completed.
 632:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *
 633:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** * Parameters:
 634:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *  retMode: Check conversion return mode. See the following table for options.
 635:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *   ADC_DelSig_1_RETURN_STATUS -   Immediately returns conversion result
 636:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *                                      status.
 637:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *   ADC_DelSig_1_WAIT_FOR_RESULT - Does not return until ADC conversion
 638:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *                                      is complete.
 639:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *
 640:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** * Return:
 641:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *  If a nonzero value is returned, the last conversion has completed.
 642:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *  If the returned value is zero, the ADC is still calculating the last result.
 643:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *
 644:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** * Global variables:
 645:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *  ADC_DelSig_1_convDone:  Used to check whether conversion is complete
 646:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *  or not for single sample mode with resolution is above 16
 647:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *
 648:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *******************************************************************************/
 649:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** uint8 ADC_DelSig_1_IsEndConversion(uint8 retMode) 
 650:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** {
 651:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c ****     uint8 status;
 652:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** 
 653:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c ****     do
 654:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c ****     {
 655:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c ****         /* Check for stop convert if conversion mode is Single Sample with
 656:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c ****         *   resolution above 16 bit
 657:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c ****         */
 658:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c ****         if(ADC_DelSig_1_stopConversion != 0u)
ARM GAS  C:\Users\Admin\AppData\Local\Temp\ccGnFHMB.s 			page 13


 659:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c ****         {
 660:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c ****             status = ADC_DelSig_1_convDone;
 661:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c ****         }
 662:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c ****         else
 663:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c ****         {
 664:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c ****             status = ADC_DelSig_1_DEC_SR_REG & ADC_DelSig_1_DEC_CONV_DONE;
 665:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c ****         }
 666:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c ****     }while((status != ADC_DelSig_1_DEC_CONV_DONE) && (retMode == ADC_DelSig_1_WAIT_FOR_RESULT));
 667:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** 
 668:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c ****     return(status);
 669:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** }
 670:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** 
 671:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** 
 672:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** /*******************************************************************************
 673:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** * Function Name: ADC_DelSig_1_GetResult8
 674:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** ********************************************************************************
 675:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *
 676:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** * Summary:
 677:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *  This function returns the result of an 8-bit conversion. If the
 678:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *  resolution is set greater than 8-bits, the LSB of the result will be
 679:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *  returned. When the ADC is configured for 8-bit single ended mode,
 680:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *  the ADC_GetResult16() function should be used instead. This
 681:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *  function returns only signed 8-bit values. The maximum positive
 682:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *  signed 8-bit value is 127, but in singled ended 8-bit mode, the
 683:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *  maximum positive value is 255.
 684:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *
 685:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** * Parameters:
 686:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *  None
 687:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *
 688:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** * Return:
 689:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *  int8: The LSB of the last ADC conversion.
 690:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *
 691:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** * Global variables:
 692:Generated_Source\PSoC5/ADC_DelSig_1.c **** *  ADC_DelSig_1_convDone:  Cleared in single sample mode with resolution
